Required treatments and services including patient actions
Arrangements for treatments/ services (when, who, and contact details)

fields.name: goals_general_role
fields.value: Patient to have a clear understanding of asthma and the patient's role in self-management.

fields.name: required_general_education
fields.value: Patient education (using patient education checklist). Ongoing asthma education by GP/ Nurse during regular reviews.

fields.name: goals_general_absent
fields.value: Absent or minimal symptoms No nocturnal or early morning symptoms. No exertional cough or wheeze. Absent or minimal reliever medication use (less than 3 times a week).

fields.name: required_general_assess
fields.value: GP to assess asthma severity when patient is stable (asthma history checklist may help) and individualise treatment. Patient to keep symptom diary or PEFR diary. Patient to adhere to preventer medication routine. Patient to take continuing responsibility for their asthma and attend for regular review.

fields.name: goals_general_control
fields.value: Patient is in control of their asthma and not vice versa Patient is able to detect any deterioration in asthma and respond appropriately. Patient knows when to and how to obtain prompt medical attention.

fields.name: required_general_formulate
fields.value: GP to formulate and provide a written asthma action plan and discuss with patient. Patient to use asthma action plan and have it reviewed regularly

fields.name: goals_lifestype_target
fields.value: Your target: Ideal: At least 30 minutes walking or equivalent 5 or more days per week

fields.name: required_lifestype_exercise
fields.value: Patient exercise routine OR As per Life scripts action plan

fields.name: required_lifestype_smoking
fields.value: Smoking cessation strategy: Consider: - Quit - Medication OR  As per Lifescripts action plan

fields.name: arrangements_lifestype_quit
fields.value: Patient to manage Quit Program Hypnotherapist GP/ nurse to monitor

fields.name: goals_biomedical_best
fields.value: Achieve best quality of life Best lung function on spirometry Best PEFR

fields.name: required_biomedical_gp
fields.value: GP – intensive asthma therapy until best lung function achieved Patient to continue with intensive asthma therapy until best lung function achieved Patient to have regular spirometry to monitor lung function

fields.name: goals_biomedical_reduce
fields.value: Reduce the frequency and severity of asthma attacks Prevent the permanent development of abnormal lung function

fields.name: required_biomedical_reduce
fields.value: GP help patient identify trigger factors Patient to avoid trigger factors if possible Patient to use preventers regularly

fields.name: goals_medication_minimum
fields.value: Minimum medication used to maintain good symptom control. No side effects or minimum side effects from medications.

fields.name: required_medication_supervise
fields.value: GP to supervise step down of medication after effective control in place for 6-12 weeks. GP/ Nurse to organize regular spirometry. Patient agree to return for planned review even when feeling ‘well’.

fields.label: Copy of GP Management Plan offered to patient?
Copy/ relevant parts of the GP Management Plan supplied to other providers?
GP Management Plan added to the patient’s records?
